The dropdown in **O3** (cell O3) contains the selected person’s name (e.g., “PETER NORONHA”). For each person row we need a formula that counts all “P” (present) entries for that person across all months.  

A suitable LibreOffice‑compatible formula is:

```
=SUM(
  COUNTIFS(Jan!$A$6:$A$49,$O$3,Jan!$B$6:$AF$49,"P"),
  COUNTIFS(Feb!$A$6:$A$49,$O$3,Feb!$B$6:$AF$49,"P"),
  COUNTIFS(Mar!$A$6:$A$49,$O$3,Mar!$B$6:$AF$49,"P"),
